  "title": "Condition",
  "description": "Specifies a set of criteria or constraints that must be satisfied for a particular business object, event, or relationship to hold or be valid. \r\n\r\nConditions:\r\n- Help define rules, constraints, or logic tied to business entities\r\n- Are reused across many domains: products, agreements, relationships, roles, and events\r\n\r\n\r\nOther definitions:\r\n- Condition is a premise upon which the fulfillment of an agreement depends \r\n\r\n- General and special arrangements, provisions, requirements, rules, specifications, and standards that form an integral part of an agreement or contract.\r\n\r\nRead more: http://www.businessdictionary.com/definition/terms-and-conditions.html",
